<div class="mb-requirement-container">
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-10020">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> </span>
      <b
        >NOTE: If meeting any of the requirements for this merit badge is
        against the Scout's religious convictions, the requirement does not have
        to be done if the Scout's parent or guardian and the proper religious
        advisors state in writing that to do so would be against religious
        convictions. The Scout's parent or guardian must also accept full
        responsibility for anything that might happen because of this exemption.
      </b>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14060">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> </span>
      <b>NOTE: </b> The official merit badge pamphlets are now free and
      downloadable
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/Athletics.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >HERE</a
      >
      or can be purchased at the
      <a href="https://www.scoutshop.org/" target="_blank ">Scout Shop.</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-10021">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-10021 mb-requirement-id-10022">
        (a) Explain to your counselor the most likely hazards you may encounter
        during athletics activities, and what you should do to anticipate, help
        prevent, mitigate, and respond to these hazards. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/yC3blqv3kp4?si=TLnyOxBv96ZuyubP"
          target="_blank"
          >Preventing Injuries in Youth Athletes (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-10021 mb-requirement-id-10023">
        (b) Show that you know first aid for injuries or illnesses that could
        occur while participating in athletics events, including sprains,
        strains, contusions, abrasions, blisters, dehydration, heat reactions,
        and concussions. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/TZqDBgiEfL8?si=RV6nOMJpa0Rc2LbT"
          target="_blank"
          >Using the Rice Method for Injuries - Rest, Ice, Compress, Elevate
          (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/oGvyiWfXB7c?si=VLL-rINKVqd871yO"
          target="_blank"
          >First Aid Treatment for Wounds (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/OcGeUdfL-s4?si=-4uuzL95rK4Is-T2"
          target="_blank"
          >Top 10 Most Common Sports Injuries (and How to Prevent Them!)
          (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-10024">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-10024 mb-requirement-id-10025">
        (a) Before completing requirements 3 and 5, have your health-care
        practitioner give you a physical examination, using the Scout Annual
        Health and Medical Record form. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.scouting.org/health-and-safety/ahmr/"
          target="_blank"
          >Annual Physical Exam (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-10024 mb-requirement-id-10026">
        (b) Explain the importance of a physical exam.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-10024 mb-requirement-id-10027">
        (c) Explain the importance of maintaining good health habits, especially
        during trainingâ€”and how the use of tobacco products, alcohol, and other
        harmful substances can negatively affect your health and your
        performance in athletic activities. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/dISDEsTr1Rc?si=4QkQnfQQjYs4GRuf"
          target="_blank"
          >Nutrition Tips for High School Athletes (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/_NUo_52vkkg?si=cy-fCChvsa8SVNQT"
          target="_blank"
          >Refusing Use of Harmful Substances (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-10024 mb-requirement-id-10028">
        (d) Explain the importance of maintaining a healthy diet. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://www.myplate.gov/eat-healthy/what-is-myplate"
          target="_blank"
          >What is MyPlate? (website)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-10029">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      Select an athletic activity that interests you, then do the following:
      <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-28062001" target="_blank"
        >Which Sport Are You Made for? Take Our 60-Second Test (website)</a
      >
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-10029 mb-requirement-id-10030">
        (a) With guidance from your counselor, establish a personal training
        program suited to the activity you have chosen. Follow this training
        program for three months. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/oRQEgV0wNtQ?si=5ZjJP2Lq6GboJ8E_"
          target="_blank"
          >Keys to Sport-Specific Training (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-10029 mb-requirement-id-10031">
        (b) Create a chart to monitor your progress during this time. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://isport360.com/7-powerful-journaling-ideas-for-youth-sports-athletes/%20"
          target="_blank"
          >7 Powerful Journaling Ideas for Youth Sports Athletes (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-10029 mb-requirement-id-10032">
        (c) Explain to your counselor the equipment necessary to participate in
        this activity and the appropriate clothing for the time of year.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.spookynooksports.com/blog/manheim/equipment-needed-to-play-sports%20"
          target="_blank"
          >Equipment Needed to Play Various Sports (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-10029 mb-requirement-id-10033">
        (d) At the end of three months, review the chart you created for
        requirement 3(b), and discuss with your counselor what progress you have
        made during training. Tell how your development has affected you
        mentally and physically. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/EHZvmAaXwfk?si=rdzKWbgW6dHqMrRO"
          target="_blank"
          >How Do You Measure Progress? (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-10034">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-10034 mb-requirement-id-10035">
        (a) Give the rules for two athletic activities, one of which is the
        activity you chose for requirement 3. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://www.rulesofsport.com/%20" target="_blank"
          >Rules of Sports (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-10034 mb-requirement-id-10036">
        (b) Discuss the importance of warming up and cooling down. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/XeEIoGMldyc?si=OXMS8XPru5l5dG7g"
          target="_blank"
          >Stretching and Warming Up (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-10034 mb-requirement-id-10037">
        (c) Explain to your counselor what an amateur athlete is and the
        differences between an amateur and a professional athlete. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Requirement%20Resources/Athletics/amateur_vs_professional.pdf"
          target="_blank"
          >What Is an Amateur (PDF)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-10034 mb-requirement-id-10038">
        (d) Discuss the traits and importance of good sportsmanship. Tell what
        role sportsmanship plays in both individual and group athletic
        activities. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/KoDu2FpU57c?si=UgLWB7uM9iY3FQBj"
          target="_blank"
          >What is Good Sportsmanship? (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/rNcfqOqDbsU?si=2C-x-nzDi7v94t50"
          target="_blank"
          >Olympians' Display of Sportsmanship Fosters Positive Attitudes
          (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/BvheyBiD6Qs?si=ZzEwe2jDYlgrIBaU"
          target="_blank"
          >What Does Sportsmanship Mean to You (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-10039">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 5. </span>
      Complete the activities in FOUR of the following options and show
      improvement over a three-month period:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-10039 mb-requirement-id-10040">
        <strong>Option 1: Sprinting</strong> <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/2twa8CAFPls?si=TFVD802jIvX0kmMW"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Sprint (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-10040 mb-requirement-id-10041">
        (a) 100-meter dash
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-10040 mb-requirement-id-10042">
        (b) 200-meter dash
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-10039 mb-requirement-id-10043">
        <strong>Option 2: Long-Distance Running</strong> <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/ZKCwpW-l_wU?si=3L7szs0IGkQdhTYR"
          target="_blank"
          >Improving Your Running Form (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-10043 mb-requirement-id-10044">
        (a) 3k run
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-10043 mb-requirement-id-10045">
        (b) 5k run
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-10039 mb-requirement-id-10046">
        <strong>Option 3: Long Jump OR High Jump</strong>
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-10046 mb-requirement-id-10047">
        (a) Running long jump OR running high jump (best of three tries)<br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/PeC29LbR94U?si=XUrZ1NjVmZetRdxl"
          target="_blank"
          >Running Long Jump (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/NLufVXI7HOQ?si=vC_x2Ym1yWiTh_H8"
          target="_blank"
          >Running High Jump (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-10046 mb-requirement-id-10048">
        (b) Standing long jump OR standing high jump (best of three tries)
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/dVgtvAXeBQw?si=nHxJ6Hm9bjzLS5pF"
          target="_blank"
          >Standing Long Jump (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/Q6mxzUBF1_Q?si=XJFxXuwaOeVRxi9A"
